139 new deaths have been recorded, with the Eastern Cape accounting for the bulk of the new fatalities with 124. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says a total of 22 206 deaths have now been recorded in South Africa. “Regrettably, 139 more COVID-19 related deaths have been reported: Eastern Cape 124, Gauteng one and Western Cape 14. This brings the total deaths to 22 206.” Tests and recoveries South Africa has conducted 5 592 663 total tests, with 26 735 of those tests conducted in the last 24-hour cycle. The private sector accounts for 58% (3 225 900) of total tests, while the public sector accounts for 42% (2 366 763). 744 780 people have recovered from the virus. --SABC--